name: Alfa
description: I have a diver down; keep well clear at slow speed.

name: Bravo
description: I am taking in, discharging, or carrying dangerous goods.

name: Charlie
description: Affirmative.

name: Delta
description: Keep clear of me; I am maneuvering with difficulty.

name: Echo
description: I am altering my course to starboard.

name: Foxtrot
description: I am disabled; communicate with me.

name: Golf
description: I require a pilot. When made by fishing vessels operating in close proximity on the fishing grounds it means: I am hauling nets.

name: Hotel
description: I have a pilot on board.

name: India
description: I am altering my course to port.

name: Juliett
description: I am on fire and have dangerous cargo; keep clear.

name: Kilo
description: I wish to communicate with you.

name: Lima
description: In harbor: The ship is under Quarantine. At sea: You should stop your vessel instantly.

name: Mike
description: My vessel is stopped and making no way through the water.

name: November
description: Negative.

name: Oscar
description: Man overboard (often attached to the man overboard pole on boats).

name: Papa
description: The Blue Peter. In harbor: All persons should report on board as the vessel is about to proceed to sea. At sea: It may be used by fishing vessels to mean: My nets have come fast upon an obstruction.

name: Quebec
description: My vessel is healthy and I request free pratique.

name: Romeo
description: No specific meaning; often used as a spacer.

name: Sierra
description: I am operating astern propulsion.

name: Tango
description: Keep clear of me; I am engaged in pair trawling.

name: Uniform
description: You are running into danger.

name: Victor
description: I require assistance.

name: Whiskey
description: I require medical assistance.

name: X-ray
description: Stop carrying out your intentions and watch for my signals.

name: Yankee
description: I am dragging my anchor.

name: Zulu
description: I require a tug. When made by fishing vessels operating in close proximity on the fishing grounds it means: I am shooting nets.
